President Biden has officially announced his intention to nominate Julie Su for Secretary of Labor. Su currently serves as the Deputy Secretary of Labor. In a statement, President Biden praised Su as a champion for workers and highlighted her accomplishments, including leading the largest state labor department in the nation, cracking down on wage theft, protecting trafficked workers, increasing the minimum wage, and establishing workplace safety standards. A wide range of elected officials, labor leaders, and community advocates have expressed their support for Su's nomination. They praised her qualifications, track record, and dedication to workers' rights. They believe that she will be an excellent Secretary of Labor and are looking forward to working with her to protect workers and strengthen the labor movement.